-- U.K. Pound Rises Versus Euro, Dollar as Central Bank Boosts Bond Program
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2012-02-09T12:07:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/u-k-pound-rises-versus-euro-dollar-as-central-bank-boosts-bond-program.html
The pound strengthened against the
euro and the dollar after the Bank of England said it would
raise its bond-buying program by 50 billion pounds ($79 billion)
to 325 billion pounds.  The U.K. currency appreciated 0.3 percent to 83.59 pence
per euro at 12:05 p.m. London time. It climbed 0.2 percent to
$1.5854.  To contact the reporter on this story:
